Name: Melodeath
Author: tritonthemusician
Description: Turned out to be a very great setting for Children of Bodom specifically. Alexi Laiho doesn't use a neck pickup and that is what this tone setting is made for, soloing and riffing using just the bridge pickup. I actually really enjoy it myself now that I have messed around with it.
Inspired by: Children of Bodom, Relentless Reckless Forever

Name: Melodic Metalcore
Author: tritonthemusician
Description: Great tone for melodic metalcore or melodic technical metal. Screams and has a good chunk to it. Best for D standard and drop C tunings. Also can be considered a good modern metal tone. If you like All That Remains or For Today and want a tone similar to theirs this is it.
Inspired by: All That Remains/For Today, Fall of Ideals/Portraits

Name: Thrash Metal Rhythm
Author: tritonthemusician
Description: This tone is all out thrash metal and groove metal very chunky and heavy. The Middle setting it just halfway to add more oomph and make it so you can do lead using this tone as well. Reverb can be added and I suggest the spring reverb if you were to do so, but only if you want.
Inspired by: Metallica/Pantera, Kill Em All/Cowboys From Hell
